Application requires this permissions for proper working. If you want to use it, turn on permissions in Settings -> Aplications -> FoWS2016 -> Permissions -> Memory or restart the aplication.

Future of Wireless Systems conference organized by scientific association Wireless Group in Wroclaw University of Technology Congress Centre is a perfect occassion to be more familiar with issues about newest techniques and systems of wireless connectibility, which was proved during editions in 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013 by atracting to this event more and more people, not only the students, but also representatives of telecommunication companies and research institutes.

Already from the first edition people frequency exceeded the expectation of organizers. In Future of Wireless Systems 2010, 200 students took part in conference. In following editions this number was still rising to the level, that conference transformed into two days event. Interesting element of conference program is student panel, where companies can listen lectures about the most interesting researches, engineering, master and doctoral thesis, made by their potential employees.

We try our best to keep improving the quality of our conference, which is a great addition to the telecommunication market and academic resourses. Taking all suggestions of our partners into account and drawing all conclusions from previous years we can assure you, that 5th edition of Future of Wireless Systems will be unique and will stay in your memory for a long time. We heartily invite you all interested for the next edition of Future of Wireless System 2016, which became the important event in calendar of telecommunication events.
14 April the main areas, which were talked during the first conference was wireless broadband systems and perspective of implementation of LTE and WiMAX.
13-14 April\nDuring this edition topics from previous edition were extended. Also additional topics appeared like multi-antenna MIMO transmission and intelligent antennas.
19 April\nIn this edition we focused on trends in future telecommuncation systems like Dynamic Spectrum Access and Cognitive Radio.
19 April\nThis conference focused mainly on modern trends and solutions in wireless systems and new solutions (SON) in standards of 3GPP group.
